column.name: Help
column.newValue: A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients. Tenant is a synonym for Client.

column.name: Help
column.newValue: An organization is a unit of your client or legal entity - examples are store, department. You can share data between organizations.

column.name: Description
column.newValue: The record is active in the system

column.name: Help
column.newValue: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reports. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for audit purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are invoices for this partner record existing. You de-activate the Business Partner and prevent that this record is used for future entries.

column.name: Help
column.newValue: The Created field indicates the TIMESTAMP that this record was created.

column.name: Help
column.newValue: The Created By field indicates the user who created this record.

column.name: Help
column.newValue: The Updated field indicates the TIMESTAMP that this record was updated.

column.name: Help
column.newValue: The Updated By field indicates the user who updated this record.

column.name: Description
column.newValue: Document sequence NUMERIC of the document

column.name: Help
column.newValue: The document NUMERIC is usually automatically generated by the system and determined by the document type of the document. If the document is not saved, the preliminary NUMERIC is displayed in "<>". If the document type of your document has no automatic document sequence defined, the field is empty if you create a new document. This is for documents which usually have an external NUMERIC (like vendor invoice). If you leave the field empty, the system will generate a document NUMERIC for you. The document sequence used for this fallback NUMERIC is defined in the "Maintain Sequence" window with the name "DocumentNo_<TableName>", where TableName is the actual name of the table (e.g. C_Order).
